Sentencas: Symmetric solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs) with the identical anode and cathode electrocatalysts show promise to reduce material and system cost while increasing the cell lifespan.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3 (BZCFY) oxide perovskite is proposed as a symmetric electrode for SSOFCs based on proton conducing electrolyte, with targets of reducing temperature and high-performance application.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Active oxygen ionic conductor and catalyst, SDC, is composited to improve the cell performance and electrode durability.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Those materials show good chemical compatibility while BZCFY is decomposed to alloy and mixed oxide composite, which significantly affects electrode activity.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SDC-BZCFY composite gives an electrode polarization resistance of 1.35-13.7 Omega cm(2) and 0.32-1.59 Omega cm(2) for hydrogen oxidation reaction and oxygen reduction reaction on the proton conducing electrolyte, BZCY, at the temperature range of 700-550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, it displays an excellent oxygen reduction kinetics with an impressive activation energy of 0.91 eV.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistances are significantly reduced in the fuel cell condition owning to the electrochemical promotion effect under opencircuit condition.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Quasi-SSOFCs with BZCY electrolyte in a thickness of 480 mu m and electrode thickness of 25 mu m give a peak power density of 114.8 and 74.3 mW cm(-2) at 650 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, SSOFC also displays acceptable durability under constant voltage operational condition for 25 h. This work highlights alternative active electrode material for symmetric solid oxide fuel cells for low temperature operation.
Titulo: BaZr0.1Co0.4Fe0.4Y0.1O3-SDC composite as quasi-symmetrical electrode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells
